Bus1_.Utility.In.Sync.comment: Indicator of whether Bus #1 and Utility are properly synchronized for paralleling. This indicator will be based on parameters such as Voltage Match, Frequency Match, and Phase Match.

Bus1_.Utility.Voltage.Match.comment: Indicator of whether voltage difference between Bus #1 and Utility is adequate for paralleling. This indicator will be based on the measured AC voltages qualified using parameters such as Voltage Tolerance.

Bus1_.Utility.Frequency.Match.comment: Indicator of whether frequency difference between Bus #1 and Utility is adequate for paralleling. This indicator will be based on the measured AC frequencies qualified using parameters such as Frequency Tolerance, Phase Tolerance, and Dwell Time.

Bus1_.Utility.Phase.Match.comment: Indicator of whether phase difference between Bus #1 and Utility is adequate for paralleling. This indicator will be based on the measured AC phase difference qualified using parameters such as Phase Tolerance and Dwell Time.

Bus1_.Utility.Dead.Bus.comment: Indicator of whether Bus #1 is considered dead for closing to the utility. This indicator will be based on parameters such as Bus #1 Voltage and dead bus threshold values.

Trans.Oil.Press.comment: Gage pressure of lubrication fluid in transmission, measured after pump.

Trans.Oil.Level.comment: Ratio of volume of transmission sump oil to recommended volume.

Clutch.Press.comment: Gage pressure of oil within a wet clutch.

Charging.System.Potential.comment: Electrical potential measured at the charging system output.

Alt.Current.comment: Measure of electrical current flow from the alternator.

Net.Battery.Current.comment: Net flow of electrical current into/out of the battery or batteries.

Keyswitch.Battery.Potential.comment: Battery potential measured at the input of the electronic control unit supplied through a keyswitch or similar switching

Battery.Potential_.Power.Input1.comment: This parameter measures the first source of battery potential as measured at the input of the ECM/actuator etc.

Network.Signal.Strength2.comment: Indicates the signal strength for the wireless communications network type.

Network.Antenna.Status2.comment: Indicates the status of the antenna for the wireless communications network type

Network.Service.Status2.comment: Indicates the status of the Service for the wireless communications network type

Network.Transceiver.Status2.comment: Indicates the status of the transceiver for the wireless communications network type

Network.Signal.Strength1.comment: Indicates the signal strength for the wireless communications network type.

Network.Antenna.Status1.comment: Indicates the status of the antenna for the wireless communications network type

Network.Service.Status1.comment: Indicates the status of the Service for the wireless communications network type

Network.Transceiver.Status1.comment: Indicates the status of the transceiver for the wireless communications network type

Voltage.Regulator.Enabled.comment: State signal indicating the Voltage regulator enabled.

Voltage.Regulator.Soft.Start.State.comment: State signal indicating the mode of the Voltage regulator soft start function.

Vltg.Rgltr.Undrfrqncy.Cmpnstn.Enbld.comment: State signal indicating the operating mode for underfrequency compensation.
